  <entry>
    <title>Bug #66 (Resolved): Getting https error when embedding YouTube videos</title>
    <link rel="alternate" href="http://opendesignengine.net/issues/66"/>
    <id>http://opendesignengine.net/issues/66</id>
    <updated>2012-06-14T15:22:43+00:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>J. Simmons</name>
    </author>
    <content type="html">
&lt;p&gt;Visit the &lt;a href="https://opendesignengine.net/projects/far-horizons-project/wiki" class="external"&gt;Far Horizons Project Wiki Page&lt;/a&gt; to see the error.  Error confirmed in Chrome and IE 9.  Error message is "This page has insecure content".&lt;/p&gt;


	&lt;p&gt;It looks like there is a new option with embedding YouTube videos for HTTPS sites.  See "Enabling HTTPS mode" on this &lt;a href="http://support.google.com/youtube/bin/answer.py?hl=en&amp;#38;answer=171780" class="external"&gt;page&lt;/a&gt;.  We should update the Youtube/Vimeo plugin to work with this feature (and check Vimeo videos for similar problem).&lt;/p&gt;    </content>
